  "content": "-size: 20px; margin-bottom: 32px;\">\n    <span class=\"corvia-wm\">corvia</span> is organizational memory for AI agents. Its inference server\n    embeds text into vectors for semantic search. I wanted to know which\n    hardware backend to default to.\n  </div>\n  <!-- Three GPU cards -->\n  <div style=\"display: flex; gap: 16px; margin-bottom: 28px;\">\n    <div style=\"flex: 1; background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-top: 4px solid var(--accent-amber); border-radius: 16px; padding: 28px; text-align: center;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 48px; margin-bottom: 12px;\">&#128187;</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 22px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-amber);\">CPU</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 8px; line-height: 1.6;\">\n        i7-12700H<br>14 cores / 20 threads<br>DDR5 39 GB\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"flex: 1; background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-top: 4px solid var(--accent-cyan); border-radius: 16px; padding: 28px; text-align: center;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 48px; margin-bottom: 12px;\">&#128296;</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 22px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-cyan);\">Intel iGPU</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 8px; line-height: 1.6;\">\n        Iris Xe (96 EU)<br>OpenVINO 2025.3<br>Shared memory\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"flex: 1; background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-top: 4px solid var(--accent-purple); border-radius: 16px; padding: 28px; text-align: center;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 48px; margin-bottom: 12px;\">&#127918;</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 22px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-purple);\">NVIDIA dGPU</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 8px; line-height: 1.6;\">\n        RTX 3060 Laptop<br>CUDA 12.8 / cuDNN 9.2<br>6 GB VRAM\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>",
